cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper focuses on the application of deep learning for structural health monitoring, specifically for crack detection and classification. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The use of acoustic emission events and spectral analysis suggests a potential overlap with computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the goal of predictive maintenance and the potential impact on future SHM technologies suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
